<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<p>Well, if you’re here reading this, you actually want to find out a bit more about <em>me</em>, as opposed to him.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">At the time of writing</span> Following updates, because life has a tendency to change directions, I’m a 20 year old college student double-majoring in Computer Engineering Technology and also Information Technology, in addition to a possible two minors on top of that, Electrical Engineering Technology and (possibly) Computer Science, if I like it well enough. I’m generally very affable, very easy to get along with, always willing to crack a (sometimes bad) joke, and overall friendly, at least until you give me a good reason not to be. Even then, I’m very much the forgive-and-forget type of person, so I’ll likely forget about it eventually. Unless it was something serious, in which case it may take a long time.</p>
<p>I’m very willing to help out anyone who needs help, so feel free to send me a PM if you need a draft looked over or something…with scips, I’m decent with tone and grammar/spelling/sentence flow stuff, though you’d be better served to go to someone else for ideas…I can get my own, but I have some slight difficulty helping others flesh out their ideas a majority of the time, which is why I don’t lurk on the Ideas and Brainstorming forum.</p>
<p>With Tales, which is so far what I write, I’m good with grammar, spelling, sentence flow, decent with character development, dialogue, dialogue flow, etc. I’ll be one of the first to tell you when your dialogue is stilted and unnatural. Like I said, if you have something you’d like looked over, feel free to PM me.</p>
<p>I’m in site19 more regularly now, but not for as long of periods of time as I'd like when I am. I'm semi-active in chat and looking to be more active on a consistent basis, which should be somewhat easy to accomplish now. I'm typically on at least once a day or more, and easy to get ahold of&#8230;just send me a .tell through Alex and I'll get it in short order.</p>
</div>
